First multiply the numerical coefficients and combine the square-root factors.

(2 √{6y⁴})(12 √{30y})
= (2·12) √{6y⁴} √{30y}
= 24 √{(6y⁴)(30y)}
= 24 √{180 y⁵}

Factor the radicand to separate perfect squares:

180 y⁵ = 36 · 5 · y⁴ · y = (6²)(y²)²·5y

Take the square roots of the perfect-square factors (6² and y⁴):

√{180 y⁵} = 6y² √{5y}

Now multiply by the coefficient outside the radical:

24 · 6y² √{5y} = 144 y² √{5y}

Simplified result:
144 y² √{5y}
